                            <comment id="13975306" author="andrew_palumbo" created="Sun, 20 Apr 2014 23:28:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Will work on this later tonight/tomorrow.  I&apos;ll remove StandardThetaTrainer and set the thetaMapper job to only run for CBayes for now.   Will deal with the possibility of optimizing by caching weights in another issue if needed.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13976333" author="andrew_palumbo" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2014 03:56:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I thought it was going to be a simpler to remove all references to the thetaNormalizer vector for Standard NB models without making too many changes, but its in there pretty deep.   I added a field to NaiveBayesModel to explicitly define it as complementary or standard (probably not a bad thing) in order to deal with all of the Serialization, validation differences, etc between Standard and Complementary models.  This way the constructor can take a null value for the thetaNormalizer vector.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I made alot of changes, so I went back and rewrote a simpler/hackish patch which doesn&apos;t touch NaiveBayesModel, but that one is much less stable and can not accept a null thetaNormalizer. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me know if there&apos;s too many changes here, and I&apos;ll submit that one (the simpler one). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13976446" author="ssc" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2014 07:36:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed, very good work, thank you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I fixed a few cosmetic things and removed the abstract class for the theta trainer as it was not needed anymore.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
